ğŸ”§ **Linux Commands**
- `ls -l` â€“ List files with permissions
- `cd /path` â€“ Change directory
- `pwd` â€“ Show current directory
- `cp src dest` â€“ Copy file/folder
- `mv src dest` â€“ Move or rename file/folder
- `rm -rf dir` â€“ Delete folder recursively
- `chmod 755 file` â€“ Set file permission to rwxr-xr-x
- `chown user:group file` â€“ Change ownership
- `groups user` â€“ Show groups for a user
- `ps aux | grep nginx` â€“ View nginx processes
- `kill <PID>` â€“ Terminate specific process
- `killall nginx` â€“ Kill all nginx processes
- `systemctl status ssh` â€“ Show SSH service status
- `systemctl restart nginx` â€“ Restart nginx
- `journalctl -xe` â€“ Show system logs

