ğŸ‘¥ **User & Group Management**
- `useradd -m -s /bin/bash user` â€“ Add user with home and shell
- `passwd user` â€“ Set/change password
- `usermod -aG sudo user` â€“ Add user to sudo group
- `groupadd devgrp` â€“ Create new group
- `usermod -aG devgrp user` â€“ Add user to group
- `id user` â€“ Show UID, GID, groups
- `cat /etc/passwd` â€“ List users
- `cat /etc/group` â€“ List groups
- `cat /etc/shadow` â€“ View password hashes (root only)

---

ğŸ’» **Bash Scripting**
- `#!/bin/bash` â€“ Shebang (interpreter path)
- `name="Kiran"` â€“ Variable assignment
- `echo "Hi $name"` â€“ Print variable
- `if [ "$name" == "Kiran" ]; then echo "Hi"; fi` â€“ Condition
- `for i in {1..3}; do echo $i; done` â€“ Loop through numbers
- `greet() { echo Hello $1; }` â€“ Define function
- `greet "Kiran"` â€“ Call function

---

ğŸ•’ **Crontab Scheduling**
- `crontab -e` â€“ Edit user crontab
- `*/2 * * * * /path/script.sh` â€“ Run every 2 minutes
- `0 0 * * 1-5 command` â€“ Run at midnight Monâ€“Fri

